            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Members appoint the statutory auditor at the annual general meeting under Section 139 of the Companies Act 2013, usually for a five year term, with the first auditor appointed by the board within thirty days of incorporation. The internal auditor is appointed by the board under Section 138, which also fixes the scope, periodicity and reporting method."
